title: Tezos Official Website
description: Tezos official website with a lot of useful information and documentation. Learn more about what makes Tezos a game changer and sign up for the newsletter.

title: Tezos Foundation
description: The Tezos Foundation's official homepage with regular news and updates about the Tezos project.

title: Tezos Commons Foundation
description: A foundation started as a grassroot movement by the community. The main objective is to grow the Tezos ecosystem by increasing the awareness and engaging the community.

title: TQ Tezos (TQ)
description: TQ Tezos (TQ) works to advance the Tezos ecosystem by creating open-source software and other public goods, providing support to projects and companies building on Tezos, and connecting the global Tezos community.

title: Tezos Southeast Asia
description: TSA is an organisation that work for adoption of Tezos in the Southeast Asia region through training, increased awareness and industrial partnerships.

title: Tezos Korea Foundation
description: A foundation set up in Korea to build and support the ecosystem there with education and industry support.

title: Tezos India Foundation
description: TIF is an independent non-profit organisation based in Bangalore, dedicated to promote the Tezos blockchain in India.

title: Tezos Japan
description: Tezos Japan supports developers and businesses and work to develop the community and awareness of Tezos in Japan.

title: Tezos China
description: A non-profit organisation based in Hong Kong that support developers and businesses in China.

title: Tezos Berlin
description: Tezos Berlin is a nonprofit that contributes to the advancement of the Tezos ecosystem. It is dedicated to fostering community, development, and collaborative efforts. Through the hosting of various events, meetings, and workshops, the organization brings a wide array of people together and provides support for them to work with and on Tezos.

title: Reddit
description: Tezos subreddit with a large and engaging community. Don't forget to subscribe here so you don't miss out the latest news and discussions about Tezos.

title: Telegram
description: Telegram groups for Tezos discussions. With an active and engaged community in your pocket.

title: TzChat
description: Tezos Riot chat is where you can you can engage with the community and find the most active community members.

title: Tezos Agora Forum
description: The Tezos Agora Forum is a place to discuss and learn about the long-term direction of the Tezos project.

title: Tezos Korea community
description: A website dedicated for the large Tezos community in South Korea.

title: TzStats
description: TzStats is a block explorer with a lot of tools for analysing the blockchain data in an intuitive way.

title: Tezblock
description: A block explorer from AirGap that gives you all the information you need about the blocks and your transactions.

title: Arronax
description: Arronax is a blockchain analytics tools for Tezos. Allows you to easily filter out data based on different conditions.

title: Better Call Dev
description: Better Call Dev is a smart contract explorer that lets you explore the code and state of contracts.

title: Tezos.id
description: Tezos.id is a block explorer rich in functionality. Maintained by the Asian community and comes with multi-language support.

title: TZ Tracker
description: A block explorer developed by Everstake that presents all the data you need in a convenient way.

title: Mininax
description: A minimalistic block explorer in retro theme, powered by Conseil.

title: Galleon
description: Desktop wallet deveoped by Cryptonomic. Available for Windows, Mac OS and Linux.

title: TezBox
description: Multiplatform wallet with DAPP-integration.

title: Kukai
description: Tezos wallet that you can access in the browser or download as a client on Windows and Linux. Also allows you to set up offline wallets, so you can store your secret key much safer.

title: Simple Staking
description: A desktop and web wallet developed by an active community member. The first one to pave the way for Trezor support.

title: AirGap
description: Smartphone wallet that let you do offline signing in a smart way. Just disconnect an old smartphone from Internet and you have created a secure air-gap to protect your private keys.

title: Cortez
description: Cortez for Android is a native mobile wallet for the Tezos blockchain.

title: Atomex
description: Multicurrency HD wallet with built-in hybrid atomic swap exchange with Tezos, Bitcoin, Ethereum

title: Tezos.blue
description: Tezos wallet, available on Google Play and Microsoft Store.

title: Wetez
description: With Wetez, you get rewards for every PoS token in your wallet.

title: Elevated Returns
description: Elevated Returns is working at tokenizing more than $1 billion worth of real-estate assets on Tezos.

title: BTG Pactual
description: Banco BTG Pactual is Latin America’s largest standalone investment bank. Together with Dalma Capital it plans to utilize the Tezos blockchain for STOs in excess of $1bn for existing and prospective token issuances.

title: Chorus Mobility
description: Chorus Mobility is focusing on research and development of the Blockchain based peer-to-peer payments protocols and decentralized applications for connected vehicles. They emerged as a winner out of 23 participants from 15 countries worldwide in the BMW-backed auto tech Blockchain competition MOBI Grand Challenge.

title: DEXter
description: DEXter is a Uniswap-inspired decentralized exchange protocol on Tezos built by the camlCase team.

title: Coase
description: Coase is building a digital collectible card game on Tezos which uses a blockchain-powered marketplace.

title: Checker
description: Checker is a software project implementing financial logic designed to help stabilize the value of a cryptographic coin with respect to an externally provided index.

title: Tezsure
description: Insurance marketplace, powered by machine learning and smart contracts on Tezos. Enabling users to create insurance products as a group.

title: My Tezos baker
description: My Tezos Baker have a large list of different delegation services. A lot of useful stats are shown that makes it easier to make an informed choice.

title: Baking Bad
description: Independent service to calculate rewards for delegation Tezos and matching it with actual received payments.

title: Tezos Nodes
description: Tezos Nodes is a rating service for public bakers. A score is calculated based on efficiency, fee and projects activity.

title: BakEndorse
description: A website that compares and tracks the performance of all the bakers.

title: Tezos Documentation
description: Technical documentation about Tezos collected in one place. Learn how to start up your own node or how to start baking.

title: Stack Exchange
description: Tezos Stack Exchange where questions meet answers.

title: Tezos Capstone
description: Tezos Capstone is designed for developers. You can learn core blockchain and Tezos concepts, and practical dApp development experience. Start your path as a Tezos blockchain developer.

title: Zastrin
description: Zastrin teaches you blockchain programming through real-world projects.

title: TQ Tezos Wiki
description: The TQ Tezos Wiki is a place to get started and learn about Tezos. It also aims to answer the frequently asked questions about the Tezos protocol & the Tezos ecosystem. This wiki aspires to be a living document that will evolve as the Tezos protocol (and ecosystem) evolves.

title: Tezos Blockstars by B9lab
description: Tezos Blockstars by B9lab. Fast-track your education to building on Tezos. Tezos Blockstars is an end-to-end program supported by experienced tutors at B9lab and designed to provide developers with the knowledge and skills needed to become industry-leading Tezos developers.

title: Michelson-tutorial by camlCase
description: An introduction to writing smart contracts on Tezos.

title: Language Paper
description: Documentation of the Michelson smart contract language. Here you learn the smart contract language for Tezos in deep.

title: Getting started with Tezos
description: An easy tutorial on how to get started with Tezos and Michelson. A great place to start for a first look into the smart contract language.

title: Lamtez
description: Lamtez is Domain-Specific Language for smart contracts, and its compiler to Michelson, Tezos' virtual machine for smart contracts execution.

title: Archetype
description: Archetype is a domain-specific language (DSL) to develop smart contracts on the Tezos blockchain, with a specific focus on the formal verification of the contract.

title: Introduction to Tezos for Developers
description: This free course provides an overview and basic understanding of blockchain technology, public and distributed networks, and Tezos.

title: Conseil
description: Conseil is a query API for the Tezos blockchain. With the JavaScript library ConseilJS it becomes easy to interact with the Tezos blockchain.

title: Eztz
description: A JavaScript library for Tezos.

title: Taquito
description: A TypeScript library suite for development on the Tezos blockchain.

title: PyTezos
description: A Python library that offers a toolset for the Tezos blockchain.

title: Go Tezos
description: A GoLang library for easily interaction with the Tezos blockchain.

title: TezosKit
description: TezosKit is a Swift SDK that makes Tezos development easy on iOS and MacOS.

title: AirGap Coin Library
description: A library that offers a unified API to prepare, sign and broadcast for Tezos among other cryptocurrencies.

title: Tplus
description: Tplus is a tool that makes it easier to manage nodes. With an easy graphical interface you can create new test enviroments with just a click. Perfect for anyone working on smart contract deployments.

title: SmartPy
description: SmartPy is a high-level smart contracts library that opens smart contract development for people familiar with the popular Python syntax. SmartPy compiles to SmartML, which in its turn compiles down to Michelson code.

title: LIGO
description: LIGO is a smart contract language that compiles down to Michelson. It comes with a pascal-like (PascaLIGO) or caml-like (CameLIGO) syntax.

title: Tezos IntelliJ
description: A plugin that enables Michelson support for all IDEs based on the IntelliJ platform.

title: Try Michelson
description: An easy tool online to try out Michelson. No need to set up a node or connect to the testnet with this handy tool.

title: Kiln
description: Kiln is a tool for baking and monitoring of the Tezos network. It provides the user with a graphical user interface and an alert system.

title: Michelson Syntax
description: Visual Studio Code extension providing syntax highlighting for Michelson and Morley source files.

title: Tezos Notifier Bot
description: Tezos Notifier Bot is a blockchain bot that can notify users on Telegram about transactions and other events on the Tezos blockchain.

title: Tezos Live
description: Tezos Live provides a SignalR (WebSocket) endpoint for anyone who want to consume events from the Tezos blockchain. You can use Tezos as a service (TaaS) or set up your own endpoint.

title: Fi
description: fi is an interpreted language for Michelson, allowing programmers to easily develop Tezos smart contracts and validate the compiled Michelson code.

title: Tezster
description: A personal development blockchain based on Javascript that lives entirely on your local machine. It will come as either a CLI with integrated GUI, has log output, and the ability to run transactions or deploy contracts against the local machine node or state of a live network such as the babylonnet, without spending any XTZ.

title: Tezos Agora
description: Tezos Agora is discussion forum and a governance explorer designed to complement the on-chain amendment process. It's the best place to visit if your want to participate in deep discussions or just learn more about Tezos governance mechanism.

title: Tezos Insider
description: Tezos Insider's mission is to offer the Tezos community useful tools, Tezos interviews, educational information, and researched tutorials by our software developers on how to use new Tezos Dapps, projects, and tools. Tezos Insider is a self-funded media venture.

title: TezDice
description: The first dice game on Tezos.

title: Tezos Projects
description: List of projects built on tezos.

title: Tezos Rocks
description: Additional indexing of Tezos web resources.
